Sentencas: Porous buffer layers for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have been investigated for many years with different thicknesses of the buffer layer in each study.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness

Sentencas: In this work, micro-tubular SOFCs having samarium-doped ceria (SDC) and gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) buffer layers are compared using the current-voltage technique, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, scanning electron microscopy, and energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness

Sentencas: The thickness of the porous SDC and GDC buffer layer is investigated systematically with the thickness varying between 0.3 and 2.0 mu m.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness

Sentencas: The power density varies between 212 and 1004 mW/cm(2) for samples having different SDC buffer layer thickness.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness

Sentencas: Comparable changes occur for the SOFCs with a GDC buffer layer, but less variation in polarization losses resulted.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness

Sentencas: Variation in electrochemical performance varies due to changes in ohmic resistance, cathode activation polarization, and interfacial reactions between the cathode and electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Micro-Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Polarization and Impedance Variation With Thin Porous Samarium-Doped Ceria and Gadolinium-Doped Ceria Buffer Layer Thickness
